#{\footnote FWWindowThread}
${\footnote FWWindowThread}
+{\footnote defbrowse}
K{\footnote FWWindowThread}
{\fs26\cf1\b FWWindowThread}\par
Declaration: 
\line{\f1
class FWWindowThread : public FWindowThread \{\line
}
\par

WYDIWYG: BIFINCL_WINDOW and BIFINCL_THREAD\par

The FWWindowThread is the base class of threads that need to use BIF/Window.\par

{\b{Caution: }}Under Windows 3.x secondary threads are limited to using 
PostMessage(). They cannot for instance create windows, use SendMessage() or 
use any API that may yield to other applications. 
\par

